@startuml Room Lifecycle — Full Sequence
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam maxMessageSize 200

title DVConf — Room Lifecycle: Create → Session → Close → Rewards

actor "User (Creator)" as User
participant "Client App" as Client
participant "Signaling\nDaemon" as Sig
participant "Relay\nDaemon" as Relay
participant "CP Daemon" as CP
participant "Validator\nDaemon" as Val
database "Sui Chain" as Chain

== 1. Room Creation & Escrow ==

User -> Client : Create room (SFU/MCU)
Client -> Chain : room_manager::create_room(\n  net_reg, manager, user_reg, relay_mode)
Chain --> Client : RoomCreated event\n(room_id, creator, relay_mode)\nstatus = PENDING

Client -> Chain : economic_layer::create_escrow(\n  net_reg, room_mgr, room_id, payment_coin)
Chain --> Client : EscrowCreated event\n(escrow_id, room_id, amount)

== 2. CP Assignment ==

CP -> Chain : poll events
Chain --> CP : RoomCreated event

note right of CP
  **Scoring Algorithm** (basis points):
  30% reputation + 25% (1/rtt)
  + 20% (1/load) + 15% stake + 10% region
end note

CP -> CP : Score all relays → pick best
CP -> CP : Pick signaling (lowest load)
CP -> Chain : room_manager::assign_relay_and_signaling(\n  net_reg, manager, cp_cap, room_id,\n  relay_id, signaling_id)
Chain --> CP : RoomAssigned event\nstatus = READY

== 3. Client Discovers Assignment ==

Client -> Chain : poll get_room_assignment(\n  manager, room_id) [every 3s]
Chain --> Client : (relay_id, signaling_id)

Client -> Chain : devInspect relay_registry::borrow_info\n→ relay endpoint_url
Client -> Chain : devInspect signaling_registry::borrow_info\n→ signaling endpoint_url

== 4. WebRTC Session ==

Client -> Sig : WebSocket connect
Client -> Sig : join(room_id, peer_id)
Sig --> Client : peer list

Client -> Relay : WebRTC connect (mediasoup)
Relay --> Client : transport params

note over Client, Relay
  Media flows through relay (SFU or MCU mode)
  User → Relay → Other Users
  No media touches the chain
end note

== 5. Validator Measurement Loop ==

Val -> Chain : poll events
Chain --> Val : EscrowCreated → escrowMap[room_id]
Chain --> Val : RoomAssigned → activeRooms[room_id].relayMinerId

loop Every 60s (configurable)
  Val -> Relay : probe metrics endpoint\n(packets, bytes, peers, latency, loss, jitter)

  Val -> Val : Build SessionProof (BCS 120 bytes)
  Val -> Val : Dual-key sign\n(main_key + session_key)

  Val -> Chain : economic_layer::submit_session_proof(\n  pubkey_public, pubkey_session,\n  sig_public, sig_session, proof_data)

  note right of Chain
    On-chain verification:
    • Derive addr from pubkey_public → must match validator
    • Derive addr from pubkey_session → must match sender
    • Verify both ed25519 signatures
    • Store proof in RoomEscrow.proofs
    • Write avg_latency → relay_registry RTT
  end note
end

== 6. Room Close & Reward Distribution ==

User -> Client : Close room
Client -> Chain : room_manager::close_room(\n  net_reg, manager, room_id)
Chain --> Client : RoomClosed event\nstatus = CLOSED

Val -> Chain : poll events
Chain --> Val : RoomClosed event

Val -> Val : Wait for MIN_PROOFS\nin escrow (poll every 5s)

Val -> Chain : economic_layer::distribute_rewards(\n  net_reg, room_mgr, escrow,\n  relay_stake)

note right of Chain
  **Reward Calculation**:
  1. Median bytes_transferred across proofs
  2. Median packet_loss_bps
  3. Quality multiplier:
     loss ≤ 2% → 10000 (excellent)
     loss ≤ 5% → 8000 (good)
     loss ≤ 10% → 5000 (acceptable)
     loss > 10% → 0 (slash relay stake)
  4. reward = BASE_RATE × median_bytes × multiplier
  5. Split: 70% relay / 15% validators / 15% CP
  6. Validator pool split by accuracy score
end note

Chain --> Val : RewardsDistributed event

@enduml
